McKinney July 14th 1863
Col A.B. Johnson
Sir I have but little
to write I only have an order from 
his (Magister?) ordering me to Report
the circumstances of the (impressment/imprisonment?)
of the (XXX) and Jackson.  (XXX)
I have refusen to do so and told 
the parties that my orders were at 
Sherman I will not make a Report
until you say so If you think it 
not improper I can Produce the 
instrument it will not  (XXX) you or 
I it will only (XXX)
is for the overXXX.  Write me and 
let me know what to do_
Respectfully
John W. Hunter
